### Key Findings

- **Implementation is solid and on-pattern**: The personalized greeting (`getGreeting()` + first name), snooze menu (Tomorrow / Next week / Pick date with `sr-only` native date input), card hierarchy (Schedule → Due → Attention → Noticed), and hover-to-reveal inline actions all match best practices from Things 3, Todoist, Range, and NNg guidelines.
- **Snooze preset pattern validated**: NNg explicitly recommends quick presets + custom date option — Reli's `SnoozeMenu` implements this exactly, with `min={getTomorrowISO()}` preventing past-date selection.
- **Hover-to-reveal actions are correct**: `md:opacity-0 md:group-hover:opacity-100` on desktop with always-visible on mobile mirrors the exact Things 3 and Todoist UX pattern.

### Gaps

- Mobile touch target size on the Done/Snooze/Chat action row may be too small (three small text links) — worth verifying in screenshot tests at 390×844
- Empty state copy is inaccurate — it only mentions Things with check-in dates, but briefing also shows calendar events and sweep findings
- `SnoozeMenu` absolute positioning may clip inside `overflow-hidden` containers on mobile

Sources:
- [NN/g — Date-Input Form Fields](https://www.nngroup.com/articles/date-input/)
- [Things 3 — Today/Upcoming/Anytime](https://culturedcode.com/things/support/articles/4001304/)
